text: {| |} MV Tulpar is a Kazakh ice-breaking and supply ship that was built in 2002 by Norwegian shipbuilder Ulstein Verft. It is based at Aktau and was originally registered to the Cayman Islands but soon moved to Kazakhstan. ==External links== * Danish shipping registry * Ulstein catalogue Category:2002 ships Category:Icebreakers Category:Ships built in Ulstein
